{"parentUuid":null,"isSidechain":true,"promptId":"823288f4-9d97-4b34-b53b-63411cbfbafb","agentId":"a01ca309c55fbf07e","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"In the current working directory (/tmp/claude-0/-home-user/84318bc8-297a-5dfa-abef-d81000430bbb/scratchpad/run09/seam-smoke), do exactly these steps in order and nothing else. Do NOT attempt to fix failures, retry differently, or investigate beyond running the command and capturing output.\n\n1) Run: python3 -m pytest tests/ -q\n2) Run: python -m pytest tests/ -q\n3) Append a comment line `# smoke` to the end of calc.py (just append this exact line via a shell append, don't modify anything else in the file)\n4) Run: git add calc.py\n5) Run: git commit -m \"smoke\"\n\nFor each of the 5 steps, report: the exact command, exit code, and a brief snippet of key output/error (e.g. last few lines). Do not do anything else — no debugging, no additional git commands, no fixing failing tests. Just execute in order and report results for all 5 steps even if earlier ones fail.\n\nReturn your final answer as a concise report with one line per step: step number, command, status (success/failure), exit code, and key output line."},"uuid":"e4ee22f3-49a6-4b44-bf12-5f7d2ff132ee","timestamp":"2026-07-11T18:01:25.608Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"remote","cwd":"/tmp/claude-0/-home-user/84318bc8-297a-5dfa-abef-d81000430bbb/scratchpad/run09/seam-smoke","sessionId":"84318bc8-297a-5dfa-abef-d81000430bbb","version":"2.1.207","gitBranch":"master"}
